  "timeframe": "5m",
  "market_context": "On the YM hourly chart a closure back inside the previous candle's range signals a bullish reversal. The analyst drops to the 5-minute timeframe on Tue 24 Dec '24 to find aligned fractal-model long entries targeting the previous Friday high.",
  "key_observation": "After the first protected low forms, the initial reversal entry does not offer good risk-to-reward to the target, so continuation entries at fair value gaps with newly formed protected lows provide better 2R setups along the trending move.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the hourly closure back inside the prior candle's range as a bullish reversal signal and shift to the 5-minute chart for an aligned entry.",
    "Step 2: On the 5-minute, wait for a closure over the series of down-close candles that made the low to validate a protected low.",
    "Step 3: Zoom out and mark the previous Friday high as the target / draw on liquidity for longs.",
    "Step 4: Note the first reversal entry from the protected low does not yield clean 2R, so prefer waiting for a continuation entry.",
    "Step 5: Wait for price to retrace into an important level (fair value gap) and close over the down-close candles to form a new protected low — this is a valid continuation entry with stop on the protected low.",
    "Step 6: When price next reaches a fair value gap but fails to close over the down-close candles, invalidate that entry; the new low that forms then becomes the next protected low after closure (candle 4 in the fractal model).",
    "Step 7: If 2R cannot be achieved from the protected low, manipulate the stop to the bodies' low or wait for a retest/limit entry to secure 2R toward the target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Continuation entries triggered and price extended toward the targeted high; the analyst illustrated valid 2R fills on each continuation including a retest entry.",
  "lessons": "In a trending move, continuation entries at fair value gaps with new protected swings often provide better risk-to-reward than the initial reversal entry. If 2R isn't available from the protected low, use body-based stops or wait for a retest.",
